body: I'll take a look. Do you know how much memory is escaping per call?

Ah, looks like its missing `api->ReleaseValue(element);` [here]( https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/master/java/src/main/native/ai_onnxruntime_OnnxSequence.c#L30) and [here](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/master/java/src/main/native/ai_onnxruntime_OnnxSequence.c#L82).
Thanks, in my example it's about 375 bytes per call.
How big are the returned Strings?

Ok. Well that seems like a lot for such short strings, but I don't know how big the OrtValue is internally as I only interact with it through the C API. I looked through the allocation path and those are the only frees missing, so I'll put in a PR with the fix shortly.

issue.title: [java] Fixing a memory leak in OnnxSequences with String keys or values.

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Description**:

I'd forgot to free the sequence when extracting String keys and values from a map contained in the sequence.

**Motivation and Context**
- Why is this change required? What problem does it solve? Fixes a small memory leak.
- If it fixes an open issue, please link to the issue here. Fixes #6471.
